# Git conventions

## Commit messages — Conventional Commits

Use the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format.

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

### Allowed types

- `feat` — new user-visible feature (MINOR in semver).
- `fix` — bug fix (PATCH in semver).
- `docs` — documentation only.
- `refactor` — code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature.
- `perf` — performance improvement.
- `test` — adding or fixing tests.
- `build` — build system, packaging, Dockerfiles, `pyproject.toml`.
- `ci` — CI configuration.
- `chore` — anything else (deps bump, tooling, formatting).

### Scopes (this repo)

Prefer one of: `manager`, `agent`, `web`, `db`, `alembic`, `deploy`,
`docs`, `scheduler`, `ingest`, `alerter`, `auth`, `jobs`. Multi-area
changes can omit the scope.

### Breaking changes

Use either `feat(api)!: ...` **or** a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer. Be
explicit about API surface changes (request/response shapes, env vars,
DB schema).

### Examples

```
feat(agent): heartbeat reports clock skew in milliseconds
fix(manager): reject job kinds outside the v1 allowlist
docs(architecture): clarify why we dropped Loki for v1
build(deploy): multi-stage Dockerfile for the manager image
refactor(ingest)!: switch logs.events partitioning from weekly to monthly

BREAKING CHANGE: existing logs.events_YYYYWW partitions must be migrated
to logs.events_YYYYMM. See docs/troubleshooting.md.
```

## Pull request template

Adapted from `awesome-cursorrules/pr-template`. Keep PRs small and focused
on a single phase item from `PLAN.md` when practical.

```markdown
## Purpose

<!-- Why is this change needed? Link the PLAN.md phase item it advances. -->

Refs: PLAN.md §X — P? <name>

## Implementation notes

<!-- Key design choices. Call out anything that touches the locked stack
     (00-project.mdc) or the v1 exclusions. -->

## Testing

- [ ] Unit tests added/updated
- [ ] Manual run against local Postgres
- [ ] Manual run against the docker-compose demo (if applicable)

## Impacts

- [ ] DB migration included (alembic)
- [ ] Env var added/changed (update `.env.example` and `docs/deployment.md`)
- [ ] API surface changed (update `docs/api.md`)
- [ ] Agent ↔ manager protocol changed (bump compat note in `docs/agent-setup.md`)

## Checklist

- [ ] Code follows `.cursor/rules/` conventions
- [ ] No introduction of Redis / Celery / Loki / Vector / mTLS / Next.js
- [ ] No new destructive job kinds in the agent runner
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] All tests passing locally

Closes #<issue>
```
